node.title: NT Police arrest man, 18, over fatal stabbing near Uluru
node.alt: Streams of water running down Uluru in a wide image showing the rock from top to bottom
node.description: Northern Territory police arrest an 18-year-old man following a fatal stabbingÂ near Uluru in Central Australia on Saturday.
node.content: ["Northern Territory police have arrested an 18-year-old man following a fatal stabbing\u00a0near Uluru in Central Australia.\u00a0", "NT Police said officers responded to reports of an aggravated assault on Saturday morning just after 9am, in the remote community of Mutitjulu in the MacDonnell region.", "Two men were allegedly\u00a0engaged in a fight when the 18-year-old man assaulted\u00a0a\u00a019-year-old man with a knife, NT Police said in\u00a0a media statement.", "The victim suffered serious injuries and died at the scene.", "Detectives from the Southern Criminal Investigation Branch travelled to the remote community yesterday to investigate the incident.", "The 18-year-old man was arrested after turning himself in to police.\u00a0", "He remains in custody.\u00a0", "Police are continuing to investigate the incident."]
